NAME
  vcontext - manage process contexts
SYNOPSIS
  vcontext [-CIM] [-f list] [-x xid] 
DESCRIPTION
  vcontext is used to create a new context, migrate to an exisiting context or
  display runtime information for a context.

  The given flag lists are converted to a flags/mask pair.;
  See AVAILABLE FLAGS below
OPTIONS
  Commands  
    -C       Create a new context
    -I       Print information about a context on stdout
    -M       Migrate to an existing context

  Options  
    -f list  Context flags
    -x xid   Context ID
LIST FORMAT STRING
  All options accepting the parameter list expect it to be in the following form:

    list = [~]<flag>,[~]<flag>,...

  A list is a comma seperated string of values available for the choosen
  listtype. To clear an already enabled flag, the value should be prefixed with
  the tilde character '~'.
AVAILABLE FLAGS
  Context Flags  
    1. INFO_LOCK  
    2. INFO_SCHED  
    3. INFO_NPROC  
    4. INFO_PRIVATE  
    5. INFO_INIT  
    6. INFO_HIDE  
    7. INFO_ULIMIT  
    8. INFO_NSPACE  
    9. SCHED_HARD  
    10. SCHED_PRIO  
    11. SCHED_PAUSE  
    12. VIRT_MEM  
    13. VIRT_UPTIME  
    14. VIRT_CPU  
    15. VIRT_LOAD  
    16. HIDE_MOUNT  
    17. HIDE_NETIF  
    18. STATE_SETUP  
    19. STATE_INIT  
    20. SC_HELPER  
    21. REBOOT_KILL  
    22. PERSISTENT  
    23. FORK_RSS  
    24. PROLIFIC  
    25. IGNEG_NICE  
    26. ONE_TIME  
    27. INIT_SET  
EXAMPLE
  To let htop view processes of all contexts:

      $ vcontext -M -x 1 -- htop
